Compress a file or directory

Example: tar -czvf arcive.tar.gz /path/to/file/or/dir/

-c = Create an archive.
-z = Compress the archive with gzip.
-v = Verbose output.
-f = Allows you to specify the filename of the archive.

Extract an Archive

Example: tar -xvzf arcive.tar.gz /path/to/file/or/dir/

x - Extract from an archive
z = tells tar to decompress the archive using gzip
v = Verbose output.
f = must be the last flag followed by tar file.
